f=Engineering/aegis/marketplace/threat-model/SKILL.md · h1:threat-model=threat model answers **"what wrong system, who it, what about it?"** independently whether any specific bug found yet. map; vulnerability discovery metal detector. good threat model tells pipeline look tells triage which findings matter. **Litmus test:** patching one line code makes entry disappear, vulnerability, threat. threat ("attacker achieves RCE untrusted media parsing") still stands after known bug fixed; vulnerability ("`dr_wav.h:412` doesn't bounds-check `chunk_size`") not. skill produces threats. Vulnerabilities appear **evidence** raises threat's likelihood score. **Invocation:** `/threat-model [bootstrap-then-interview\|bootstrap\|interview] <target-dir> [flags]` · h2:Step Route mode=Parse `$ARGUMENTS`: · h2:Step Route mode=\| First token \| Route to \| · h2:Step Route mode=\|---\|---\| · h2:Step Route mode=\| `interview` \| Read `interview.md` in this directory and follow it. \| · h2:Step Route mode=\| `bootstrap` \| Read `bootstrap.md` in this directory and follow it. \| · h2:Step Route mode=\| `bootstrap-then-interview` \| Bootstrap first, then interview seeded from the draft. See below. \| · h2:Step Route mode=\| anything else, or empty \| Ask the user: **"Is someone who owns or built this system available to answer questions in this session?"** Yes and the codebase is checked out → recommend `bootstrap-then-interview`. Yes but no codebase → `interview.md`. No → `bootstrap.md`. \| · h2:Step Route mode=modes write artifact (`THREAT_MODEL.md`, schema `schema.md`) downstream consumers (pipeline `recon`/`judge`, verifier agents) need know which mode produced it. · h2:Step Route mode=\| \| `interview` \| `bootstrap` \| · h2:Step Route mode=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Step Route mode=\| **Needs** \| An application owner present in the session \| A local checkout; optionally past vulns \| · h2:Step Route mode=\| **Method** \| Four-question framework: conversational walk through *what are we working on → what can go wrong → what are we going to do about it → did we do a good job* \| Five stages: parallel research swarm → synthesize sections 1-3 + vuln table → generalize vulns into threat classes → STRIDE gap-fill → emit \| · h2:Step Route mode=\| **Best for** \| New systems, design reviews, systems where the risk lives in business logic the code doesn't show \| Inherited systems, third-party code, OSS dependencies, anything with a CVE history \| · h2:Step Route mode=\| **Provenance tag** \| `interview` \| `bootstrap` \| · h2:Step Route mode=**Context durability.** Interview mode multi-turn; tool results early reads evicted before you need them. stay resilient: · h2:Step Route mode=**not** read `interview.md` `bootstrap.md` full front. Read · h2:Step Route mode=mode file (or relevant section it) **at point you need it**, one question stage time. · h2:Step Route mode=re-read Read tool refused "file unchanged", prior · h2:Step Route mode=result evicted; reload `cat <path>` Bash instead. **Interview backbone** (so you proceed even `interview.md` unavailable mid-session): · h2:Step Route mode=\| Q \| Question \| Fills schema sections \| · h2:Step Route mode=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Step Route mode=\| Q1 \| What are we working on? \| section 1 context, section 2 assets, section 3 entry points \| · h2:Step Route mode=\| Q2 \| What can go wrong? \| section 4 threat rows (id, threat, actor, surface, asset) \| · h2:Step Route mode=\| Q3 \| What are we going to do about it? \| section 4 impact/likelihood/status/controls; section 5 deprioritized; section 8 recommended mitigations \| · h2:Step Route mode=\| Q4 \| Did we do a good job? \| validate ranking, coverage check, section 6 open questions \| · h3:`bootstrap-then-interview` mode=owner available *and* codebase checked out, recommended path: owner's time goes refining code-grounded draft instead describing system scratch. Tell owner: "I'll read code first come back draft (about 5-10 min), we'll walk together. Want that, you rather start cold?" proceed they opt in; otherwise fall back `interview.md`. Read `bootstrap.md` follow end-to-end. Write `<target-dir>/THREAT_MODEL.md`. Immediately continue interview mode: read `interview.md` follow `--seed <target-dir>/THREAT_MODEL.md` effect. section open questions bootstrap become your Q1-Q4 prompts; owner confirms, corrects, adds rather starting nothing. Overwrite `<target-dir>/THREAT_MODEL.md` refined model. Set provenance `mode: bootstrap-then-interview`. flow available manually: run `bootstrap` first, `interview --seed <THREAT_MODEL.md>` later session. · h2:References=[docs/security.md](../../../docs/security.md) and · h2:References=[docs/prompting.md](../../../docs/prompting.md) engagement-context authorization framing skill inherits.